## Introduction to GIT
    git init ... initialize local git repo
    git remote add origin [REPO] ... point local repo to GitHub
    clone [REPO] ... clone to current working directory

__Basic GitHub commands__

1. [add] new files to index 
2. [commit] changes to local repo
3. [push] new contents to remote repository

<code>
    git add . ... add all new files to index

    git add -u ... update tracking for changed names or deletions
    git add -A ... do both of the above

    git commit -m 'message' ... stage for local repo, description
    git push ... send changes to remote repo
</code>

__Branching__

<code>
    git checkout -b BRANCHNAME ... create a branch from a repo
    git branch ... show your active branch
    git checkout BRANCHNAME ... switch your active branch to BRANCHNAME
</code>

__Pull requests__

Once you pushed changes to your branch of the repo, create a [pull]
request to merge your changes into another repo. The request must be
completed on the website.